transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. Joanna speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I need to end my refill subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay, I can assist you with that. Can I get your name and date of birth, please?

Speaker 2: Ronald Baker, 32263.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you. I have your account here, and I do see that you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 2: I just wanted you to know, sir, that you are not required to get your refills on a monthly recurring basis.

Speaker 1: We are not a subscription. We are a telehealth.

Speaker 2: And that prescription written by the doctor was made available to you with refills.

Speaker 1: And as our customer, you can decide how you want to set up your account.

Speaker 2: You can modify the frequency and quantity at any time or put a pause on your account for up to six months.

Speaker 1: Was there a reason for the cancellation today?

Speaker 2: I don't need this much.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that makes sense. And that's exactly why we're so flexible with our customers about frequency and orders.

Speaker 2: So, you know, we understand that life circumstances change, and, you know, people have different needs.

Speaker 1: So currently it's set up to receive a refill every month, but I can remove that and set it up for every three months,

Speaker 2: every four months, every five months, every six months.

Speaker 1: I want to get out of the refills period.

Speaker 2: Okay. Not a problem.

Speaker 1: Again, what I can do is I can put a hold on it until July.

Speaker 2: That way if you want to call in and place an order before then, you'll still have access to your prescription.

Speaker 1: Otherwise, if I cancel it entirely, it will cancel that prescription available to you.

Speaker 2: And when you want to place a future order, we won't be able to fulfill that order without a prescription.

Speaker 1: Okay. Put me on hold until July.

Speaker 2: Excellent. I'll go ahead and place it on a hold.

Speaker 1: You're not going to receive any refills.

Speaker 2: And just let us know if you want to place an order before then or if you want to extend that hold.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right. Thank you, sir, for being a VIP status customer. Have a beautiful day.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Thank you. Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
